§fFind some flint and bang it (right click) on some hard surface to get flint shards.

§nTIP:
§n§rMake sure you use the topside of whatever surface you find.

§9§fMake a knife with a flint shard and a stick.

§nTIP:
§fYou don't need wood to get sticks. Leaves might help.

§9you can't drink water out of this.§f

Use the knife to cut some vegetation and get some plant fibers. From there, you can use three plant fibers to make plant string.

§nTIP:
§fWith plants in your offhand, you can use your knife to cut it into sticks and plant fibers.

§9what the fuck

§fMake a flint hatchet. Finally, you can get some wood and make planks by right-clicking the top of a log with the axe.

§9im actually an asshole, you're welcome.§f

Final thing before you can go, make sure you know how to craft the crafting station. They are useful for keeping items in the table when you leave the GUI so they don't just spill everywhere.

§9its too much

§fTo start working with Tinker's Construct, you'll need a couple of tables: the Stencil Table and the Part Builder.

§nTIP:
§fYou might also want a Pattern Chest.

§9im making tools

§fFor tools, you'll need to make a Tool Station to put all your parts together in.

§nTIP:
§fPlace all your tables adjacent to one another to more easily access all of them through the UI.

§9im making armor

§fFor armor, you'll need to make an Armor Station to put all your parts together in.

§nTIP:
§fPlace all your tables adjacent to one another to more easily access all of them through the UI.

§9oh my god make some patterns holy§9§9

§fMake some patterns using the Stencil Table. Place a blank pattern in the left-hand slot and select a pattern to make on the side.

§nTIP:
§fDon't shift click.

§9bro just make the stuff

§fBuild a pickaxe using the patterns you made. You will need a tool rod, a tool binding, and a pickaxe head.

Start by using patterns and wood in the Part Builder to make the tool parts. Then, in the Tool Station, select the tool you want to build and put the parts in.

§nTIP:
§rREALLY don't shift click when you build parts.

§9bro just make the stuff

§fBuild a chestplate using the patterns you made. You will need armor trim, armor plates, and a chestplate core.

Start by using patterns and wood in the Part Builder to make the tool parts. Then, in the Armor Station, select the armor piece you want to build and put the parts in.

§nTIP:
§rREALLY don't shift click when you build parts.

§9go to bed please

§fWith your newfound knowledge of utilizing the tinkers' tables, create a full armor and tool set.
